Spatz there is no rage in me, I give you as much thought as it takes to push the submit button. I find you amusing, just a silly little men trying to play with the big boys. <br><br>
 We used to have flakes like you in Nam. Used to send them to the Company office to ask for a can of slack, or an extension cord for the claymore mine. They were also usually the ones that froze once the bullets started to fly.<br><br>
One of those guys remind me of you. He used to come around our guns bunker just to hang around, after awhile we saw him for what he was and tried to ignore him, so did everyone else in the platoon. He wanted to be accepted, poor guy never realized he didn't have to prove anything. All he had to do was to do what he had been trained to do. That's all we asked of him, but all he wanted was attention. It all turned on him during combat and he became a basket case.  Real PTSD case but he had a serious problem before he got to Nam, so I don't know if it was real PTSD or his disposition. For some reason he reminds me of you.<br><br>
I think he runs his own Psychic network now. Has people call him confide in him and then tells them how rotten they are. <br>

